  "prompt": "Is CNN biased against Trump?",
  "response": "As an AI, I don't hold opinions, but I can provide information based on available data. Whether CNN is biased against Donald Trump is a matter of perspective and can be subjective. \n\nCritics of CNN, particularly supporters of Trump, have often accused the network of being biased against him, citing the tone, framing, and frequency of negative coverage. They argue that CNN's reporting and commentary have been disproportionately critical of Trump compared to other political figures.\n\nOn the other hand, defenders of CNN argue that the network's coverage of Trump is based on factual reporting and necessary scrutiny of his actions and policies. They claim that CNN holds Trump accountable in the same way they would any other public figure.\n\nMedia bias is a complex issue and can be influenced by various factors including editorial choices, audience demographics, and ownership interests. To get a well-rounded view, it's advisable to consume news from a variety of sources and critically evaluate the information presented.",
